Reasoning: The paper discusses the theoretical foundations of deep learning and proposes a physical perspective to understand its internal mechanism. This aligns with the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) which focuses on the development and analysis of machine learning algorithms. The paper also discusses the neural network of deep learning as a physical system, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a theoretical direction for the further development of deep learning, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the limitations of deep learning, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents calculation methods for various deep learning techniques, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
